6. Leave the file completely empty. Do not type anything inside it. Just save it.

### Step 2: Push the Update to GitHub
Now, we need to send this new file up to the `main` branch so GitHub can see it.

Open your VS Code terminal (make sure you are on the `main` branch) and run:
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Added .nojekyll to bypass GitHub Pages default builder"
git push origin main